reviews.review_text: Fantastic cocktails and well made food. Service was friendly and the restaurant is clean and tidy. What more can you ask for? Oh, the prices are reasonable too!

Had a great experience at Chambar! We were seated very quickly and our waitress Shayla was amazing. Food and drinks came out in a timely manner, food was great, atmosphere was great. Overall an amazing first impression. Will absolutely be coming back :)

An unforgettable dining experience! Chambar Restaurant impressed me with its delectable cuisine and charming ambiance. The menu offers a delightful mix of traditional and innovative dishes, and their attention to using locally-sourced ingredients is commendable. The staffs passion for food and top-notch service made the evening even more enjoyable. If youre a food enthusiast looking for a standout gem, Chambar is the place to be!

One of my favorite places to dine in Vancouver, from start to finish this place cares a lot about their guest experience. Professional, polished service. Kitchen is always putting out impeccable food, menu composition is stellar, something for everyone. Ive been for Brunch and Dinner many times and have always had the Best time here. First time having their espresso martini and honestly one of the best I have ever had! Thank you for doing such an amazing job and taking such great care of your patrons! Dietary restrictions: I have a gluten and dairy allergy and the server had great knowledge of the menu and took great care in making recommendations.

Came to Chambar for a wedding, the entire basement was the private event, great for small events, can get stuffy. Service was amazing, but most importantly the food was so good. I had the lamb shank, it was super tender, fall off the bone delicious. There was enough for 2 meals. Definitely has the old town vibe, but yet not tacky. Every server was nice and the bartender was great all night. Will be back on my own to try their full menu.

We initially planned on going to Jam, as Victoria has one that we love. Upon arrival, the line went back a quarter of the block. So we started looking at reviews right outside of Chamber restaurant trying to figure out our next step. It was then that we saw it served brunch as well and had excellent reviews. We put our name down for a reso for 2 and were sat 20 minutes later at the bar. This Belgian-themed restaurant has gorgeous exposed wood with thick posts and cross beams creating a cozy atmosphere.  They have put a lot of money into the design of this place and I appreciated the beauty. Brunch was not your traditional bennies and bacon and eggs. I am a big breakfast person. I need breakfast food to start my day. Especially on the road. Chambers menu has a light grasp on the traditional breakfast, but in the best way possible. There were still eggs perfectly cooked, sausage full of flavor and a beautiful integration of fruit sides in the way of  julienned apples, and pineapple salsa. The balance of our dishes was impressive. I ate the pork dish quicker than I would normally eat my breakfast. Each bite and combination of flavors tasting like more. I also had the lemon drop with sparkling wine, which was a very refreshing beverage, having already had my morning coffee intake. The prices are higher end, but the dishes are well thought out and well worth the price.

Loved the atmosphere and the food at Chambar! I would 10/10 recommend the cornbread to share for the table (or for yourself). The waffles and topping options were really fun to mix and match, the pistachio rose water topping being a pleasant surprise. I wasn t very impressed with the coffee or London fogs, but I will chalk this one up to a personal preference.

Absolutely incredible value! The restaurant was well-staffed and the service was attentive. The menu has a wide range of unique plates with the option of nice sides for add ons. We sat on the heated patio for lunch and even though it was a breezy fall Vancouver day, we were cozy - I was even offered a blanket! We will return again!! Pictured: -chai tea almond milk latte -Kingston crown mocktail -fricassee -shakshuka

Delicious surprise. Originally going to Jam but line was too long to wait. Everything we had here was great, nice presentation and very flavorful. Shakshuka is a must try. Probably more enjoyable than our original choice.

Absolutely amazing food. They were also very good with my food allergies. Not only was I accommodated I had flavorful and amazing food. Went for brunch, which is hard to get my egg, dairy, and gluten allergy accommodated but it was amazing. They have an amazing gluten free bread, without egg and dairy. Their bacon and apple side was the most incredible bacon I ve had in forever. Must get. Was told their dinner menu is extremely gluten free, dairy free, and egg free friendly.
Crazy food! Im ready to live here. The Roti de Boeuf is unforgettable. Tender Belgian waffles, Moules Frites were excellent. Very attentive staff

My aunt and uncle were visiting and I think I couldn t have booked a better place. I, of course, was drawn by the reviews and the positive feedback of other patrons  experiences, but these were not fluff marketing ploys. The food was absolutely amazing! The dishes were unique in both presentation and taste. If you want something DIFFERENT and novel, then this is the place. It may sound corny, but the medley of ingredients that were activating my taste buds was incredible. I m really curious what the other dishes taste like and that s why it s worth revisiting. The vibe was upbeat and you are made to get into that personable mindset, as the staff members seem to be - from the reception to the initial greeting at the table and the overall service. I would have preferred the tables and seats to be a bit farther apart for more semi-privacy, but packing in that many patrons also made business sense. It was my uncle s treat and I think the servers already got the cue from that considering he was the more senior at our table and staff members were engaging him more, but the servers also were not short of properly addressing us when it was our turn to say something. Acknowledgement of presence was never short and I loved it about their service. They re absolutely attentive and also steadfast. If the water levels on glasses were low, someone was on it and they had that open-hands stance about their demeanor in engaging us. Someone would swing by every now and then to check in on us and the staff members were not snoots. This is probably the best experience I ve had in a while. The restaurant is worth a try EXPERIENCING.

I cannot say enough about the service. We found out our server was only in her role for two weeks. She was professional, presentable and knew the menu inside out. You can tell the staff there is cohesively working as one unit and that they really loved being part of the team. When our server was not able to come to our table I believe the general manager popped by - he already knew that we had dietary restrictions. This place is a staple and absolutely one of my favourite places in Vancouver.

Some of the best food I ve ever eaten and the service was great! all around an amazing restaurant. Our waitress Alicja was fantastic. First time trying duck, and I m glad it was here because of how amazing it was!

dinner makes the final stop for my friends stagette. our server was so lovely and patient. everything I had was delicious, though I especially loved the foie fras terrine with truffled french toast. what a wonderful way to wrap up the day.

Fantastic brunch! Food was excellent and reasonably priced for the serving size/quality. Angie took great care of me and gave some nice recommendations of places to stop by around the area. Will be coming back next time I m in town!

Chambar has a beautiful environment, brick walls and gorgeous lights. We sat at the bar and had excellent service. We ordered the beef short ribs and brochette du porc (meat heavy). The brunch meals were good, beef was so tender. My favourite part of the meal however was the mini waffles and dips. The waffles had a unique slightly chewy texture and the dips were fabulous. Would definitely return!
The server recommended this strong french beer and it got me going    first thing in the morning. Wish i remembered the name tho. It was busy but worth the wait
What a great wine selection! Cheryl was our server and she was so cool. The food was delicious and the overall atmosphere was chill.

Had an amazing meal. My friend with whom I was eating was ESL and sort of misunderstood the server when he asked us if we wanted stuff and then demanded for the stuff later but the server was so accommodating and patient with us, really appreciate that. She was visiting from Quebec and I m so glad I brought her here the food was delicious. She s also Moroccan and she rated their Tajin 7/10. Our favourite dish of everything was the Congolese Moules Frites, they were delicious and I highly recommend you get some bread on the side to dip into it.

I came to Chambar pre Covid and it was one of my fav place for mussels. This time around I was craving for mussels and wanted to come back to this restaurant. The restaurant is very modern with a hip vibe. I arrived during brunch, but I didn t want brunch so had to wait until 11:30 am when they open their lunch and dinner menus. So I had some Mimosas cocktail while I waited. The mimosas was made with freshly squeezed orange juice. They also have fresh grape fruit and watermelon juice. I sat at the bar since the place was packed and I didn t have reservations. The bar tenders were so nice and very amazing service. I ordered the Congolaise coconut curry mussels with sour dough bread and a side of fries. It was as amazing as I imagined! The mussels were so fresh and completely hit the spot! Will definitely come back next time I m in Vancouver.

Went there around 5 PM on Friday, was able to get in without a reservation. Service was very friendly. Drink orders were taken quickly and served. It became mildly busier and our food orders took a bit longer, which can be forgiven. The food and drink were excellent. Flatbread appetizer was great, never had anything like it before. The Vegetarian curry was very light and delicious according to my fellow diner (Not for my personal taste, however.) The large portion of lamb was incredibly tender, fell off the bone. Thought I have to admit, the giant bok-choy(?) in my dish was a bit odd, in my opinion. Leftovers were packed up for me. Will definitely go back in the future for Brunch!

Very busy place in DT Vancouver.  We went there on weekday evening and only was able to get a seat at the bar.  Server was excellent, well informed of their menu and customer skillset was also good.  Food were interesting and tasted pretty good.  Portion size was also on the good side.  Place is pretty big and there are nice patio seatings which seem to be preferred options for many especially in good weather.  Located conveniently beside the skytrain station, it is quite easy visit too.

Chambar was a fantastic choice for brunch. I got a mimosa plus the Brochette de Porc and it  fueled me for the majority of the day. The tomatillo pineapple salsa was the perfect sweet/acidic counterpart to the savory sausages & potatoes. Chambar is on my list of restaurants to explore the dinner menu and consult their sommelier  on my next visit to Vancouver.

We stumbled on this place after deciding waiting in a hour plus line for the Jam Cafe was not an option. Life is just too short to wait in line. Anyway- no exaggeration this was best brunch I ve ever had. The food came quickly, and was amazing. Seriously I ll probably be chasing the tail of this dragon forever. The staff are friendly and efficient. Do yourself a favour and come eat here.

Dinner here was great, as always. Amazing food, service and ambience. Was expecting to have steak frites but when that wasn t on the menu we ordered the bison carpaccio and it was sooo good. The Congolese mussels and broth are so delicious and I m always surprised how many are in there! Very filling. They have such a great liquor menu too, including hard-to-find Belgian Trappist beers, and Fortaleza tequila. Fun to sit at the bar and converse with the friendly and knowledgeable staff.

rustic but modern vibe with very knowledgeable and attentive staff! shakshouka (sub halloumi cheese with avocado) is amazing! Not super traditional as it comes with a side of lentils and pistachios. the ratatouille is the other vegetarian and dairy free option (but does have eggs). I recommend the vanilla latte with oat milk! they ve got a few latte options like lavender too and chai

Definitely recommend here for a group dinner. We got a bunch of things to share, and everything was delicious. The mussels were great, and I recommend that you get a side of bread to soak up the sauce! Highlights of the meal were the flatbread and the duck gnocchi.
Well done Chambar! Food and beer list was on point. Highly recommend the brunch menu. Perfect portions and identifiable ingredients.

Our first time at Chambar. Great customer service and amazing atmosphere. We ordered dishes that we don t normally see from other restaurants. Did not disappoint. The waffles are a good ending to our meal.
Love the food, the service, and the drink list! Definitely coming back!!

We went to go to jam cafe but the line was ridic. The waffles and coffee were excellent here. Wife had the bacon and apple and it was great too. Scott was a good lad and ga d good recommendations on places in gastown. Recommend.

I went there for my wifes birthday. The atmosphere was great. The food was creative and also tasted great. The restaurant was a little bit too busy so servers were not unable to attend so quickly, everything else was awesome. Id love to go there again.
Came here for weekend brunch. Nothing to complain about. Food was all delicious. Drinks were well made. Great decor and ambiance.
Great brunch! I really liked their waffle as well. I would come back for dinner

Have been coming here for many years and plan to come back as long as they are open for business. My wife even organized 2 Christmas parties at the Chambar. Amazing atmosphere and very delicious fine dining choices. Their Belgian waffles are the best I have ever had anywhere and the sauce choices are great. Also a large selection of beer, wine and quality spirits. Excellent place for a date!

I love restaurants the surprise me with their unique menus.  It was by chance that we went for brunch at Chambar on a Saturday morning.  Breakfast was truly surprising with picture perfect presentation and unique ingredients.  The food is so tasty from the first bite.  Next time, I would like to get an extra serving of the fried cheese and beans.  PLEASE.

Surprisingly one of the best waffles I ve ever had. Chambar is amazing. The ambiance, the staff and the impeccable service. The food was yummy, I ended up over eating. The cappuccino was as hot as I like (not a lot of places can get my version of temperature of coffee right). Going back again for Waffles

Phenomenal food and services. I had the plan about a week ago but found out that the 21st edition of Vancouver dine-out week was ongoing, so there was no regular menu. Presentations are joyful, and overall they managed to have very balanced tastes. They also had some savory combinations in their puree that are not commonly found somewhere else. The staff there explained the food very well. The dinner was also a wonderful celebration of the lunar New Year.
Best brunch place ever! We had La Truite Fumee, the Shakshuka and the waffle. The Shakshuka was the best I ve ever eaten. Highly recommend!!

Vancouver dine out 2023 Appetizers: le boeuf was great, nicely seasoned and cooked just right. Foie gras (slight price upgrade) was paired with thick French toast, balsamic vinegar, and a cranberry (?) ice slush. It was a generous slice of foie gras and somewhat too much. I loved how the slush helped cleanse the palate between bites as it was very rich. Main: Venison meatball and gnocchi was great. The game meat was rich and gnocchi wasnt overly oily. The Arctic char was the highlight of the night. It was so tender and juicy with crisp seared skin, and the sides balance the flavors perfectly. One of the best fish dish Ive ever had! Dessert: lorange sanguine was a good assortment of desserts, with a variety of flavor and texture. Poire et chocolat was indulgent and the ganache was heavenly rich, however I dont agree with the pear pairing even though it was cooked well. Would come back next year for this menu again! Very well done.

The moule frites is my favourite dish of all time! A must get. The sour dough is also tasty. I love that they have mocktail options. The vibes inside are fine dining with none of the expectations of that. It s a really great place to stop for dinner.

As always, consistently amazing. The room, the service and the food. Let them do what they know best and you won t be disappointed.  Hats off to Connor for making the night very memorable and personal, a professional of his craft that goes above and beyond!!

I booked the private dining room at Chambar for a 20-person holiday work dinner. The entire experience, from top to bottom, exceeded my expectations. The service was excellent, the food delicious, the atmosphere/lighting/music just right, and the communication from the staff before and during the event: perfect. It was the best work dinner weve had, and I want to thank Chambar for such an excellent experience. Well definitely be back!
Lovely little brunch spot. Enjoyed everything we ordered and the coffee drinks were great.  Service was prompt, vibe was enjoyable and restrooms were clean. Will definitely be back

Went for brunch on Saturday and didn t wait long for a table. Great menu and one of the best brunches we ve had. Really enjoyed it. Attentive friendly service and good atmosphere. The food was excellent and great Bloody Marys.
Booked the Chambar for our anniversary and we had a great time. They even had a surprise for us for the event. We had the duck and it was beyond expectation.

Aww.... the ambiance!  The feel of the place!  Crisp clean and delicious food.  Excellent service.  Kids friendly.  True rustic elegance.  Outstanding beer selections.  Thank you Fathers Day day for the excuse to be allowed to be dragged (not even one scream or kick) into this beautiful place by my wife and kids.  :o)

Our entire dining experience was wonderful, thanks to Connor! We ordered the veal and the duck confit, both dishes taste great! Connor gave us recommendations on how to end both dishes with the perfect bite. Also, the cheesecake doughnuts are just delectable! Everything was recommended by Connor. It s refreshing to meet someone who really enjoys good food and is willing to share their love of food with other people. Connor concluded the night with a nice magic trick. The restaurant is lucky to have him. We ll definitely be back!
Such a great experience. The meal was amazing, the staff were so friendly, and the flavours were top notch.

We went here during dine out Vancouver. They had a good 3 course menu offering and we had heard great things. They didnt disappoint! From blue cheese and fig martinis to amazing delicious applies and entrees, this is a go to place. Food came out promptly and very well played and prepared. Stop by and enjoy everything they have on their menu!

Made reservations for brunch, which is amazing, no need to wait in line   the experience was impeccable from the moment we walked-in, seats were comfortable, tables were clean, table setting was high quality. Best of all, service was top notch, kindness, respect, and professionalism. To top it all off, my brunch and my drink were tasty and delicious.

Although this wasnt the restaurant I initially intended to go to, they had seats available, and Im so thankful they did, because it was a great experience and I will definitely be back. The atmosphere inside is great, with a great menu selection. The cocktails were great and the waffles were delicious as well. A great dining experience with great service.

Great meal and ambiance!  Our group of 4 had the hanger steak, duck confit and the butternut squash - all were prepared very well and were delicious.  Also had the pavlova and creme caramel for dessert, and they were incredible! Service was a bit ambivalent, but still polite. All in all, a truly enjoyable evening. Parking: Parking lot is directly across the street as well as street parking is normally available, however there was an event that evening, seriously impacting parking availability
Easy going, laid back atmosphere while still being an elevated experience. Great Belgian options. Attentive, fast, and personable service.

We had a great dinner at Chambar. The staff was very friendly, fast and courteous. We had reservations to 5PM, to get to the Cancuks game starting at 7PM. We ordered 2 mains, staggered, starting with the mussels then the braised tagine lamb shank. and a couple drinks. The food was delicious, came out fast and looked great. We were able to enjoy our dinner, and get to the game with lots of time to spare. Would recommend Chambar to anyone, and the service to get us in and out for the game was fantastic.

The ambiance and service of Chambar is excellent.  Its cozy and lively and was quite busy by the time we left...tables are too close together for my liking.  The food came out quickly, looked delicious and good portion size for each dish.  I would give 4.5 star overall, bc I did not prefer some of the fusion of flavors on the dishes.

We first visited Chambar over a decade ago with my partner as a special treat when we were poor students. We have been there 3 times in total and they walk a fine line between exciting and new with some traditional elements to their food. Whatever we order its always tasty. The staff always give us exceptional service.

The staff and the food are both top notch here. My first experience at this restaurant will have me taking friends and family back for sure! I got the ratatouille and the misses had a waffle & salad. Again, the service was friendly, the food tasted amazing, and the  venue was lovely.

Date: January 19, 2020 Server: Tommy Total: $54.60 My brother took me here for a delightful breakfast. I got the Omelette w/ avocado and kombucha while he got the Paella w/ egg and drip coffee. For someone whos least favourite food is omelette, Im pleased to say that this was one of the most delightful omelettes Ive ever had. That is high praise. Entrees were both a little less than $20 dollars. The kombucha, however, will make you run the bill at $7. I hope that cultured bacteria helps me live longer for that price. Just get the coffee. What makes this place shine is its interior design. One of the best atmospheric dining experiences for that alone. Chambar normally specializes in dinner service, where the building takes on a whole new look, but features breakfast on the weekend. A safe bet if its your first date, and you want to win the lady over. Vegetarian options: I believe my omelette was vegetarian. Parking: EasyPark Lot 2 but the parking might run up the bill even further

It was my first time here. Chambar was very remarkable. We went for brunch and didn t have a reservation. Nevertheless, the hostess was very friendly and nice and got us a table right away which was very much appreciated! We were blown how spacious and big with it being spread over two floors.  What a cool decor with the red bricks and aesthetics! We ordered the Paella and La Truite Fumee breakfast sandwich. Both dishes were flavourful and delectable ! I really enjoyed the paella with a fun twist as it had curried orzo instead of the Bomba rice. It was a such creative dish and very delicious! The service was great as well. She was very knowledgeable about the menu and took our dietary restrictions and allergies into consideration which is again much appreciated. The Belgian waffle was such a treat with the two sauces, chocolate lavender and the white pistachio chocolate sauce. We were very impressed at the food s quality, service and flavours. Totally recommend if you re wanting great brunch without waiting in line/queue for hours! Will return again
First time here. Food was very good especially the scampi and tuna tartar.  Didnt like the rabbit. The staff was amazing and will be the main reason for my return. Very professional.

Great first experience at Chambar. Visited for brunch  and was awesome. The entrance was a little strange and awkward as theres a massive curtain right at the front door. Once through that, the space was open, beautiful and well decorated. Food was fantastic and the service was spot on. Price was reasonable given the size of the restaurant, location and quality of food!

Awesome food and great service. We were originally going to a different place but, there was a 45min line to get in. Luckily Chambar was just walking distance. Great brunch was had along with the coquotte mussels. The salted caramel and dark chocolate waffles we had for dessert was really great too. Just the right amount of sweetness!
One of my favourite restaurants in the city. I literally cannot go enough times to this place. Both brunch and dinner are amazing. Some of my go-to dishes are the lamb tagine and charcuterie board.

Came here for brunch with my partner last Saturday around 12:30pm, we both loved the food. Ive been many times before but am always blown away each time. The staff were kind, and we were told a 45 minute wait, 10 minutes later I got a text to get back! That was amazing. The corn bread was delicious, the waffles perfect as usual, and the sausages were so good! We completely finished everything on our plates. The staff are very kind and understanding, as well as make you feel like a valued patron. Will definitely be coming in for dinner soon, too. I missed dining at Chambar. As a side note, I feel like you can dress up here, or dine more casually. Love the atmosphere youve created and the environment, and the food!! Thank you again, it was a great time!
Our go to dinner spot before a Broadway play. The atmosphere at Chambar is comfortable. The staff has always been very helpful and friendly. The food is amazing and the cocktails are refreshing.

Chambar is our favourite spot in the City. Whenever we are looking for high quality food and service, one of our first options is Chambar with it classy yet casual atmosphere. The limited number of items on the menu, is indicative of how much effort has been put for its perfection. If you like fois gras, give Chambar s a try.

Had a fantastic experience here for my birthday. The food was absolutely amazing. Every bite was jam packed with flavour. The Le Boeuf dish was a great starter to start up your appetite. The candied morels in the dish were a great sweetness to go with the hanger steak. The mussels a la Congalise were a must have, I would definitely recommend getting their grilled sour dough to soak up the lovely soup. The Tajine lamb shank main was explosive with flavour. It was a wide medley of flavours, with quite a few sweet elements to it, but it was a great balanced dish. It was further improved with the harrisa and raita option which is absolutely necessary to the dish in my opinion. In regards to service the folks at the host stand they were very accommodating, as we had arrived for our reservation nearly 30 minutes too early. We were able to get seated right away which was fantastic. Although this was due to a table being available anyways. Our server Alicja was an absolute gem. She was very attentive and well versed in the menu. Her advice on portion sizing would have been well received if only the menu looked less appetizing. She recommended a glass of wine to go with my main dish which paired perfectly. A small speed bump to the whole experience was a small delay between our appetizers and mains. She amended the situation with free biscuits and chocolates at the end of the meal (biscuits and chocolate will fix just about any mistake or problem, but I am low maintenance). Overall the experience was great. Sure it was not picture perfect, but a mistake is no longer a mistake when it is corrected. I very much look forward to coming here in the future. And I would recommend it to everyone else in the city as well.

A gorgeous place for dinner and a date. Our server (forgot her name) was a lovely Korean Canadian lady. She was new but pretty good and friendly. I loved the charcuterie and Autumn salad for starters. Mussels are to die for especially the soup. I recommend trying lamb shank for mains if you like spices and curries. Its 6 hours braised shank that wont let you down. It was a perfect night with lovely people from the chamber restaurant.
We enjoyed having our Saturday morning brunch at Chambar Great service, nice ambiance and delicious food . We ordered Fricassee and Waffles. They were both quite tasty.
I went here for a friend s birthday and sharing a bunch of waffles was such a perfect brunch experience. The pistachio rose water and milk chocolate lavender sauces were to die for.

We thoroughly enjoyed our brunch at Chambar. We started with a delicious cocktail recommended by our server. The pork breakfast plate was very tasty, especially the sausage with the perfect hit of spice and flavor. The coffee was fantastic. And a waffle with salted caramel sauce was the perfect way to finish our meal. Service was top notch as well. Two thumbs up from both of us!

Chambar was on my list for so long, and I am glad I was finally able to dine there! Flatbread was extremely delicious: an explosion of flavors! Drinks were very nice too right level of strength and taste! Service was great too. I m glad that they strictly check vaccine cards and IDs at the door. My only displeasure was that for reservations they require a credit card guarantee. I understand it but it s very different from the industry practice.

Absolutely delightful experience! The ambiance was charming, the staff was incredibly friendly and attentive, and the food was a culinary masterpiece. I cant wait to come back and explore more of their menu. Highly recommended!
Consistently still one of the best restaurants in Vancouver. Open space, modern, consistent service and ambience. Best for brunch. Lavender lattes, mussels and frites and wine Food : 4/5

Visited here for brunch. The food was amazing. The staff accommodated my medium-sized party and were attentive, helpful, and friendly the whole time. I pre-booked online and they were highly communicative, even with a couple changes I made to the reservation beforehand. Pricing is very fair, especially for the quality of food and presentation. The ambiance is really cool with lots of wood and natural light. Spacing was great; didn t feel squished despite being quite busy. Check out the light fixtures; really unique. Washrooms were roomy and clean. I will definitely be going back.

Got pretty good experience there, the vibe is really cozy and nice. The food is also nice! The waitress Gemma is very kind, but another waitress I asked to take off my plates seemed obviously reluctant to serve me. I remembered she is pretty tall. I would recommend Moules Frites and the dessert ganache. The mussels with the tomato sauce is really tasty. Also, I suggest to taste the ganache with both the ice cream and ruby chantilly, it s not so sweet and is a good dessert to try!

Amazing restaurant, fantastic service! We sat at the bar and the bartenders were super friendly and helpful. Food was absolutely delicious. They were very accommodating for my dairy allergy, I was even able to have a dessert, which is rare for me! It was a great experience and I hope to go back!

We had Ros greet us at the door. Very sweet girl, great first impression of the restaurant. She had us sit at our server Alicias (spelling?) table. She was so friendly and gave us perfect recommendations and answered all of our many questions thoroughly. She is very good at her job and you can tell she enjoys meeting new people. Order The Blue Fig

The brunch here was lovely. The fresh waffles were amazing - they were warm and soft and a must try! The portions here are also quite good - the fruitand yoghurt was way larger than I expected. There is a good selection of breakfast/brunch food here. This place is quite popular so I would recommend booking in advance if you dont want to wait.

There is a multitude of culinary delights at this establishment. From there great selection of craft beer two well-appointed cocktails. The space absolutely delightful thought through from top to bottom. Gray bathrooms friendly stop delightful food I found the menu a little confusing wow they really brought it home with a true culinary delight. This establishment is a real winner

Such a beautiful restaurant and delicious food. Albacore tuna and arctic char were the star of the show! The short rib was so tender it just fell apart, so good! I thought the bison appetizer had too much whole peppercorn but was fine otherwise. The warm sticky toffee creme caramel so delicious, on the sweeter side but was such a nice way to end off the evening.
Their dine out menu is great! Nice setup of the restaurant, servers are friendly and quick to respond. All the food was great, portion is very good.

Today was the second time we came in 4 days. We ordered the Fricasse again. The coffees were good. Interesting infused flavours in their food and drinks. I thought the waffles could be better though. Food is beautifully presented, nice ambience, good service. I would recommend breakfast and brunch here.

Came to Chambar for brunch. Ordered the Talisman Pale Ale, which is an Amber beer. They have a pretty good selection of drinks available. I like how the menu is digital and separated into categories. Makes it easier for those dining in only for food, or only for drinks. We got the Paella and the La Saucisse. For the Paella, it was a different style of paella that Im normally used to. The rice they use was a bit different from other Paella Ive had. But overall it was good. The cornbread in the other dish was fantastic. I truly enjoyed it. The waffles was pretty standard from other places. For the ambience of the restaurant, its fairly upscale and has a fancy bar. Would be a good location for a drink and have a nice meal. Shoutout to their staff Kaya. She was very friendly and accommodating since we needed to rush out to catch a flight. Overall I will recommend for you to visit this restaurant for your brunch,  dinner or drink destination.

I think this is my favourite place on Vancouver. I went for brunch, which was excellent on top of great service. Noticed they had an excellent beer list so decided to come back later in the day to sample it....absolutely sublime! Staff are great, venue is incredible and the person doing the interior design deserves an award. Ill be back!
Best place for mussels! Plump and juicy in an exceptionally fresh and tasty broth of your choice. Decent portions. Good service in a cozy but spacious setting.
Foooooods are great!!! Wanna visit every quarterly. Because they change the menu quarterly(or seasons?)
Looking for exotic & yummy   new flavours to try? Chambar it s the right place to go, Belgian    inspired cuisine, with different and interesting tweaks!   Great service too  !
The BEST drinks in Vancouver. Phenomenal in taste and balance. Ambience was also nice, and Brendan was a great bartender. I fully plan on visiting again soon

We came here on a Sunday for brunch. There was a wonderful selection of dishes and traditional brunch items. We sat outside on the terrace. They offer mimosas and other cocktails as well as juice and coffee. We had the granola, fruit and yoghurt, the cassoulet and a few ordered waffles. Just be aware the waffles are somewhat small so if you are hungry you may want to order 2. The cassoulet was a wonderful mix of black eyed beans, fried egg, kale, sausage, chicken and chimichurri. It was very flavorful and light. The food came out in a timely manner and our server was very attentive.

This place deserve 7 starts not only 5! It is just amazing in all terms and standards! Lovely atmosphere, excellent service, beautiful design, amazing food, very generous portions, wide choices and so much more! I choose to take my best girlfriends there for her birthday diner because of the great reviews and we simply end up being stunned with the quality of the service! We had so much fun everything was excellent we ate so much until we didnt had place for desert anymore but still since the chef knew that we having a birthday dinner he made sure we get a small complimentary sweets with a happy birthday note. We were so happy with this beautiful treat!!! Everything was excellent but the mussels were exceptional definitely it is a must try!!! I recommend and recommend and recommend again!!! It is already my favourite place in downtown Vancouver and cant wait to go soon for brunch it looks like it is soo yummy!!!

Because of air pollution concerns, outside seating was closed: but we managed well indoors. Excellent moule frites (available with variations, too) and a superb selection of Belgian and other beers (and lots more besides). Great smiling service!
Very delicious food, coming from a foodie one of the best tasting restaurants in Vancouver!

Went there for dinner. Totally enjoyed the food and drink a lot! They have pretty good collection of alcohol drinks. The lamb we had was so good! Desserts were tasty too!! I like their atmosphere too!

This place is so good we came by for both brunch and dinner! Their breakfast is very tasty, the plates aren t too big so you dont leave too tired. For dinner- I recommend you skip right to the muscles!! No need to ever order anything else, it is that good. Also, skip the charcuterie, not that great

We had the most lovely time here at Chambar. All staff were welcoming and friendly. The cocktails and mussels were absolutely delicious. Everything about the space felt very intentional. I would recommend for anyone looking to treat themselves to a nice night out!
We came here for breakfast the day after our wedding and the staff/manager were amazing! They brought us complimentary sparkling wine and dessert. Plus the food is awesome!

Excellent restaurant with ample outdoor patio.  Wonderful service, great food.  A little pricey but worth it. Some vegetarian choices and inventive brunch menu.  Pita chips make the shakshuka more of a dip than a sauce.  Romantic ambience in the evening. Clean well stocked toilets.
